file operations¶

open() allows to open a file (or creates it if it does not exits)

write is used to write on the file

read is used to read from the file

In [89]:
f=open('grocery.txt',"w") # "w" open to write
f.write("Apples\n")
f.write("eggs\n")
f.write("milk\n")
f.write("Supreme pizza")
f.close()

close() close the file
